adjectives.description: asphaltic (comparative more asphaltic, superlative most asphaltic)

entries.meaning: Resembling, containing, or relating to asphalt or bitumen.
(obsolete) Of or relating to the Dead Sea (salt lake between Jordan and Israel).
examples: As Sodomes Apples, neere th’Asphalticke lake,
Of specious shew, yet touch’t, to ashes turning,
So are sinnes poysons sweete, yet bane to take;
